Also had the potato salad which was ace. Can’t fault them and would definitely order again - definitely up there with Bari and J.P Grazianos for best sandwiches in Chicago. 👌

I got there at 11:22am and walked out at 12:02pm. It took 40 mins to get the 5 subs. The guy in front of me had a 30 sub order and so many grub hub and uber eats drivers kept coming in to pick up online orders; plus other people kept coming in off the street to get a sub. The phone kept ringing and the lady wasn’t answering the phone. LOL She shut all the online food delivery services off because they were too busy. It was kind of funny actually.

The owners are great here. They also own the hardware store next door. In fact this store front use to be part of the hardware store until they added on the sandwich shop.  It was a brilliant move by the owners to start making subs here. Down the street is Bari which is the original Italian chicago sub place with a line that goes out the door at lunch time. This place is a great alternative to waiting in the line. Is the sandwich the same? No but it's darn good. In fact, many businesses have copied Bari and started serving subs like Dmatos Bakery & JP Graziano. This sub thing is really competitive in this neighborhood. In fact, it's like a sub war. Everyone has their favorite. I recommend you go out there and find out which one you love the best.

The best sandwich shop in Chiccago.Darlene does a great job with this classic shop..like it's out of a old Hollywood noir movie but taking place in the west loop of Chicago.i love the roast beef..marone..plus the drinks are very local, that this LA boy,always has questions but not to many if you know what I mean..lol

Ralph the delivery guy is also awesome. If you go, try the Turkey pesto Mayo special (which has been the special since I started going three years ago). I swoon every time I take a bite.
